Great dude

comment: Dr. Wittman is very knowledgeable of all things related to CS. He is an excellent professor but sometimes makes you feel a little stupid in front of the class.

Teaching us new software was always last minute and consisted of a 5 min. tutorial. I don't think he even knew what he was doing at times. The final project wasn't based on a grade, just his observations.

He likes to be very vague and demands things in a certain way. It gets to be very stressful but in the long run is helpful because he's trying to prepare us for the working world. Dry humour. He's growing on me.
LOVED HIM! I have another class with him and I can't wait. He's great! Makes class fun and really cares about the students
Dr. Spence is just a fantastic guy. Not to mention the fact that he brings candy to FYS. Great guy, loved having him for First year seminar and Band
Dr. Spence (you fools spelled his name wronge) is an amazing professor who will do anything for his students. He has a lot of knowledge to share.
I find this professor very unhelpful, very disorganzied, and does not respond to emails or give feedback at all for her class. I find her very sarcastic, rude and try to avoid her at all possible.
Dr. Waughen is my favorite professor on campus. She's not even in my department. She's very helpful in and out of class.

One of the best professors at Etown. Always comes in class and wants to know any new or exciting things in our lives. She is nice, helpful, and my favorite professor. I encourage everyone to take a course with her.
Only downfall to this professor is she let's her kids grade some of your work... and they usually mess up your grading. She'll fix it for you though if you show her you did the work.
Super easy class. Hilarious prof! Always very personable and cares about her students both in and out of class. Slows down when necessary, making sure that no one ever falls behind.

Great teacher and honestly a great person. He can tell if something's bothering a student and goes out of his way to make sure they're okay. He tries to make the class as understandable as possible, and help you out when he can.

Justin Badgerow. What can I say about Justin Badgerow. Great teacher, very helpful and thorough. Definitely enjoyes what he does, and not to mention seeing his face at 8 a.m. makes theory more tolerable. Adorable man!
He is my piano teacher, and he is insanely talented! Very crazy, but that's what makes him fun.
Very knowledgeable. Everyone likes him. Somewhat quirky.

My favourite professor. Dr. Pretz offers difficult course material at an in-depth level and with a passion to deliver the most up-to-date information and theory available. She is dedicated to her students but won't go too far out of her way to make sure you're alright if your usual grades are low. If she sees you slip, she will reach out to help.

Dr. Pretz is an amazing professor. She is super passionate about the subjects of intelligence and creativity. She really knows her stuff and her enthusiasm is infectious. Take this class, it is worth your time!!!!

This woman is from Yale. She is extremely passionate about her subject but because of that, she goes too fast. Students can't comprehend as well b/c while she is talking fast, we are trying to copy the lengthy notes from the P.P. Also, her questions don't make sense sometimes so you have to ask more than once. Good luck if you have her!
An amazing professor even though I didn't do well in accounting. He is very funny and soft-spoken and will help you with anything that you need.
Prof Ellicker is by far my favorite professor I've ever had! He makes the subject clear and easy to understand, all while creating a fun environment!
loved being in his class
Prof Elicker is the ideal professor for someone who wants to learn accounting casually. He would extend deadlines and would help u understand the concepts.
Prof E was one of the best accounting teacher I have ever had. He made sure his students understood the material while making learning fun.

He makes sure you understand the material in class. He repeats himself, goes back if you need it, and does examples in class. If you need help talk to him afterwards and he is happy to help. Plus he also stops halfway through class for a break and to ask interesting questions.

Professor Elicker was hands down one of my favorite professors at Etown. If you are not good at accounting, ask for help and he will happily make time for you. You do not have to go to class, but final grades can be swayed upon attendance.

Excellent professor. Very caring, helpful. Willing to meet outside of class to tutor. Great humor. Material is difficult, but he explains it very well. Definitely get him as a professor if you get the chance. Work is manageable and homework is very helpful. overall, great.
Excepts a  lot from you, tests are really hard
brought competancy and credibility. extremely thorough and knowledgeable.

Dr. Newsome was the best Professor I had this semester. Im taking another class with him in the Spring. Hes really supportive of first years and helps you whenever you need it. Overall amazing professor.
ratingTags: Amazing lectures--Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: He doesn't use the textbook (although it is required), but the primary-sources book is used regularly. A decent amount of reading, but he is a knowledgable professor and a really great person.

So boring! I took west civ II for my core. Choose a different class or different prof. He's so boring and monotonous. Hard to stay awake. A lot of reading and a lot of pop quizzes. Two book reports. Tough grader.
Good teacher. Helpful. Decent amount of reading, but you don't really need to read the textbook (DO read the sourcebook). Do the work, and you'll get a decent grade.

Newsome is a down-to-the-point professor who will not give much leeway when it comes to work. There is alot of reading to do for this class and 2 tests and 2 essays More or less Newsome is helpful and definitely knows what he is teaching but this is not an easy course if you are not a history major.
New professor. Adapting to the school. Lots of information! No tests besides midterm and final. Information needed will be found on the powerpoints. Easy grade on all papers!

Amazing prof she is incredibly helpful and caring beyond any teacher I've had before. A little strict with APA citations but otherwise a pretty easy class. She does all she can to help and is extremely approachable. Truly one of the best.
One of the best profs I've had; if not the best. Text book is not very crucial because she covers everything in class. Very helpful and makes class interesting with her lively personality.
Professor Kanenberg truly cares about her students. She is awesome at clearly stating necessary information! Very helpful, understanding and an all around great professor.

She is the nicest professor ever and very considerate. If we didn't go over it in class it won't be on the test. Theres no real need to read the book since all her material will be covered in class, the only reason to read would be so you could participate in class. Overall, she's very reasonable and truly just wants to see you succeed.
Great professor. One of the best. There for her students.

This is a professor that will go out of her way to help you. Puts a lot of emphasis on outside class learning. Getting to know her on a personal level will help a lot i.e. talk to her before/after classes, let her know your interests in the classes, strengths and weaknesses.

Dr. Atwood is a really sweet lady. She explains everything well and her being really young, she connects with her students. I got really disappointed when I found I wouldn't have any other classes with her next semester. Made the class very fun. She grades tough because she wants us to succeed. Grades hard on drafts so you know what to do correctly
Made the class harder than it should have been on purpose.  But overall, still a good teacher

ED250 Language & Literacy Development is not a very difficult class for the most part. The lectures were solely discussion-based and engaging. Bellew does well in explaining teaching methods with examples. Exams are easy but long. However, get ready to receive picky feedback on lesson plans.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: Professor Bellew was really helpful when I took her class. She is also super nice.
She's an excellent teacher! Super nice and really knows her stuff!

Classes mainly consist of a PowerPoint and group activity. Tests are very easy and follow power points exactly. Be prepared for date changes on the syllabus. Not the most interesting class but she is very helpful and understanding even though not always entirely organized.

Pushes back due dates a lot but doesn't go on from a subject until everyone understands. Very helpful if you have issues completing work on time. Takes attendance and notices when people aren't there.
Tough to follow.  Too many moving parts to assignments. Unclear direction.

Insists on doing a lot of the prep work himself, so assignments/rubrics/grades are often given back late or with little time for revision. Laid back as far as deadlines go, even for rewrites. Will email you constantly if you're missing even the slightest part of an assignment. Pretty chill in his discussions, but can sometimes say awkward things.
ratingTags: SO MANY PAPERS--Tests? Not many--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: He was my first year adviser and is one of most unorganized teachers I have ever come across. Swanson gives a lot of work, and fails to grade any of it. Three months into the course and I have no knowledge as to what my grade is because he is lazy. He is an extremely hard grader; he expects you to put 100% into the course while he puts 35% into it
He is a really great guy. Very demanding in his work, but makes up for that with his lenience and laid back style. He is great to have conversations with, and is very knowledgeable.

Classroom discussion is the best part of this class. The professor consistently holds the interest of the students in the class. The plays which are read from the anthology are never dull and always contain relevant and intriguing subject matter.

hes a really cool guy and even if you do the bare minimum youll pass his class and hes a pretty lenient grader which is nice, unlike some of the other professors in the department. hes also very understanding

Very nice guy, but unfortunately, not very good at teaching. Obviously knows what he's talking about, but does a terrible job of making US understand what he's talking about. Often goes on complicated chemistry side notes without explaining the material in a way that makes any sense. Tests WAY too hard given how little he actually teaches.

I thoroughly enjoyed the musicology class that all music students have to take as a senior. As long as you don't do your assignments the night before they're due, you're fine. He really cares about your success and is happy to help you out. He may come across as stand offish, but he is a very nice and very wise man. Super passionate for music!
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Honestly, to pass Dr. Bomberger's classes, you have to be interested or at least feign interest. He really is a sweet man if you just seem to care. Go to his office once or twice for help, even if you feel like you don't really need it, for your semester projects for history. There are benefits for your paper's grade if you do.

I may be in the minority, but I enjoyed taking classes with Dr. Bomberger! He may com across as harsh, but if you are struggling or just want to learn more, than he'll be more than happy to help you out! Just don't be lazy, and you'll be fine!

Dr. Bomberger is a real jerk most of the time. He is ALWAYS right, no matter if he's wrong or not. And don't even try to talk to him over email about anything. He'll just not respond. Can't wait to be done with him.
Very strange man. Socially just odd. He seems very smart though and you could learn a lot from him...but I wouldn't want to. Just me.
good class, but can get boring and tiresome, but music majors ur forced to like it! lol
Very easy class, even if you can't draw :) Nice professor, you just have to show up to all the classes!

Best professor I've ever had. Really good at communication with students - when covid unexpectedly came around he was completely on the ball with keeping in touch with us and would email us about every small change to make us feel secure, in a period where some of my professors just completely lost contact with me. Really cares!!

Great teacher. If language isn't your thing, you might struggle a little. But you have to TRY to get anything less than a B. Just try your best & he will recognize your effort. Quiz heavy class & usually some homework. Nothing too bad though. Definitely attend class because a lot of class is verbal language practice.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Participation matters

comment: Overall, a very good professor. He's humorous and tries to call on everyone in the class. The class is a little homework and quiz heavy, but he encourages people to come to him for help. I felt like I learned a lot of Japanese in his class.

Takahashi-sensei was amazing. He paced class well, used all of our time to the fullest extent, and really cared about his students. He really goes out of his way to help us; he's my favorite professor yet. So thankful to study Japanese with him!

Best teacher ever, Provides solid work, with solid class time. He is truly the key to unlocking your future if you are a Japanese major etc. He will stay around and help with everything. Any question, any amount of extra work. He appreciates his job and we appreciate him.

Most amazing teacher I've ever had. Understands that life can be busy, but don't slack too much or you'll fall behind. Always willing to help and will accommodate office hours for you if you need them. Truly cares about his students and wants to help them the best he can

Takahashi Sensei is the best teacher I've ever had. He's always there to help and gives quality feedback on all assignments. He truly cares about all of his students and makes sure everyone is included.  Every class is packed with fun activities, partner practice, and lots of laughs. There's never a dull moment and every class is worthwhile.
Excellent professor!! very funny and nice and willing to work with you to get a good grade

One of the most helpful professors I've ever had. Went above and beyond to make sure that students were comfortable with material. Keeps class interesting with spontaneous activities (he might play the guitar for you one day). Not a super-hard grader but expects a high amount of effort from students. One of my favorite professors.

Takahashi sensei is such an amazing teacher! He works so hard to make sure you know what he is teaching. He is a little tough, but if you have questions, he will answer them. Seriously, best teacher I've had.

Takahashi Sensei is honestly the best teacher I have ever had. He is funny and engaging and can make the material easy to understand. He is challenging however, and expects you to work hard. What I have found though, is that you learn to respect him so much that you don't want to let him down. He is an amazing teacher.

For someone who isn't a dancer, this class was definitely the most challenging experience. She doesn't give any feedback on assignments. She doesn't give any specific guidelines for assignments. If you aren't a dancer, do yourself a favor and DO NOT TAKE A CLASS of hers.

I've taken all of pontzs dance classes. She really pushed me to become a better dancer. She is fun and you learn many different styles of dance. She's also crazy and has you do ballet to lady gaga. I miss her classes, even the feeling of not being able to walk the rest of the week
Some writing assignments involved, but pretty short and not difficult.  She is really intense with the warmups and exercises though.
Great professor!

He knows his stuff, and is passionate about anthropology. Unfortunately, he is terrible at teaching, and it was almost impossible not to fall asleep during class. I probably could have skipped every single day and received the same grade, but he takes attendance every class. Avoid this guy unless you love anthropology as much as he does.

He isn't mean, but he isn't really fun either and the class is really boring. No real material to it. And sure as hell shouldn't be so early. But assignments were often poorly described on what he wanted. You kind of just guess. Not a bad guy by any means but what exactly he is trying to teach us...I couldn't tell you.

I didn't learn much from this class. He has a lot of opportunities to earn good grades so it's pretty easy to earn an A if you put in the work. The thing that bothered me most was how unclear he was in his expectations. Many times we were left wondering what to do for an assignment even after he explained it twice. It's also at 7:45AM which stinks.

First thing is hes very funny and has a heavy but understandable Russian accent. He even says himself he doesnt know why hes teaching so get ready because he isnt quite the best. In my honest opinion I love his class but youll have to teach yourself and study A LOT I have him at psu Harrisburg currently. Hilarious when he cusses. Confusing

By far one of the worst professors. Hes a nice guy and pretty funny but terrible at teaching. He doesnt do practice problems or even teach. His PowerPoints arent his and he doesnt make the exams. His exams are from another source so he doesnt know whats on it. DONT TAKE HIM!!!!

The Economist portion of classes was easy and laid back. Should pay attention and take notes for the Game Theory parts. Few tests were given and were always open book and notebook. Very helpful with essays.

His lectures are short and sweet, but his tests are hard compared to the lighthearted classes. He is always available, so always ask any questions. He also looks out for you if you get to know him. He'll send opportunities and advice your way.

Game theory is the hardest class I had to take EVER!!! and I am a senior. Game is a very interesting topic but the level of math and the level of detail are super hard. Dmitri is funny prof and is available to help. I just wish for more examples.
Best Economics Professor at Etown. Knows his stuff and explains well. Not easy though.
Dmitriy is a great fellow.  As long as you read the book, you should be fine.
Very nice guy. The course is fast and you have to study for quizzes, tests, and read the book. Not an easy class.
Good Prof. You HAVE TO read the book and you will do well.
Super nice professor. Always available to help. Lots of quizzes and hard test though. Read the book to study.
Hard class but the prof is funny and super helpful. You got to study though.

Dr. Krichevskiy was new this year to Etown. I never had a desire to take economics but needed to being a BA major. I was totally fine in Macro with another professor, but after Micro with this guy, I HATED economics. If you can take with another professor, DO IT. Don't get me wrong, he is a smart man, but a terrible prof.

Know your facts ad be ready to defend your opinion within the course. Understand that while she is a very tough grader and papers need to be almost perfect and that the more you write, the higher your grade will be. I cannot stress this enough but be ready to talk in class, as she is not afraid of the silence.

Dr. Shah is a great teacher! Very passionate about what she teaches and she keeps it interesting.  Both classes (Criminology and Intro to CJ) are fairly easy - if you go to class, pay attention, and participate you'll get a good grade! Highly recommend :)

The class is quite a lot of fun. You really do learn a lot. There's a lot of note taking, but she puts the powerpoints online anyway. She loves doing random read alouds to the class and showing videos. Awesome teacher!
She tends to add a lot of readings on at the last minute, and the reading reflections are kind of tedious, but it is a pretty easy class.

Great teacher, great guy! Informative, collaborative, loose class atmosphere. The man is easy to respect and knowledgable on the subject, but is also willing to learn from students. Just like us, we all can learn from each other. He has a great leadership style and I'd work for him. Valuable lessons were learned about the dev process.

His delivery is like a pregame pep talk, and he's a coach, so that makes sense. Relies heavily on book and powerpoints. Knows his history but I found myself disagreeing with him a lot. Different world views, I suppose. Overall a decent prof but not convincing. He added some good marketing history. You'll learn a lot about e-commerce from the book.
Very nice and very easy, she was very excited about the subject which made the desire to go to class a lot easier. I definitely recommend taking her if you can!

Professor Russ comes off to  be very intimidating and stern, but her instruction is not that difficult to follow. She is someone who you can learn a lot from, and cares what she is teaching about. I recommend her highly.
Very stern, She pretty much expects you to know pronunciation perfectly and is not patient with you, she will skip over you if you take too long to answer (around 8-10 seconds)

Dr. Hoffman's gen chem course is lecture-based and moves at a moderate pace. He's very smart and teaches the material clearly. WARNING: online assignment due dates were not constant for us- most were due at eight am, but not all (don't procrastinate). Focus more on your notes rather than the book when studying.

Dr. Hoffman wants to see you do well.  He is passionate about chemistry and puts a lot of extra time into preparing for his courses, (a lot more than other professors).  If you are having trouble go talk to him, but do NOT wait until the last minute.  Go to class, put in the time, ask for help.

Dr. Hoffman does not help you understand the material. Went to his office for extra help and he just confused me more. Highly suggest not taking him. Everyone I have talked to agrees with me. If you have a choice, do not take him.
Great teacher, very intelligent, pay attention in lecture and you will do fine

I've had Dr. Estrada for three classes so far, and he is by far my favorite professor.  His teaching quality is above and beyond that of most professors. He does an excellent job explaining course material so that students can easily understand it, and he is very passionate about teaching. He is definitely there to see his students excel!

His exams are incredibly difficult but he is great lecturer and always willing to give you feedback. If you show up to class, take good notes, and are willing to study like crazy; you'll do well. If you don't do well, there's a good chance he'll check in you. He's one of those professors who genuinely cares about his students.

Dr. Cecala is a fantastic professor and person. Extremely accommodating and friendly. He legitimately cares about the well being of his students and it shows!  He is also very humble and will be honest when he's unsure about a topic (unlike other professors with large egos).Take as many courses as you can from him!

Dr. Cecala is a great professor who really loves his students. But because he only teaches upper level course he expects a decent amount of work out of his students. As long as you do the readings before class and go to his office hours for questions you have he isn't all that bad of a professor
He is a generally nice and likable professor, but be careful because he likes to play games

Be prepared for a ridiculous amount of studying (I'm not kidding). I gained important knowledge however his tests are extremely difficult and they are the only thing you are graded on. Helpful at office hours but sometimes gives more information then is really necessary which results in further confusion.

She is a new prof. this semester & serves as an adjunct. Her class is pretty easy & mostly common sense stuff. Her class can be interesting but after the first 30 mins., it becomes boring. Currently, the class is from 5:30-8:45pm & we're supposed to get 10min breaks. That didn't last long though. She is a meh prof. & is unclear answering questions.

Absolutely awful. His lectures are unclear,  and painfully long. His attitude in class is very judgmental and he does not slow down to thoroughly explain something if someone doesn't understand. The class is literally a powerpoint and him lecturing for over an hour. You'll learn and understand more if you just read the textbook yourself.

He is the worst professor I have ever had. He has no idea how to teach and if you need to take probability and statistics DO NOT torture yourself and take it with him. He's horrible and doesn't explain a single thing. The tests are extremely hard and he doesn't go over how to do problems so you're basically screwed for the entire class. He's awful.

Makes mistakes on the notes "on purpose" if you believe that... Very unclear during lecture and will hassle students if they don't have the answers.  If you're taking prob stats take someone else. This isn't worth the effort for a core class.

Impossible to understand, makes class uninteresting with very plain and repetitive powerpoints. Tests are filled with trick questions. Out of all the stuff in the book he could have touched base on, he went for all the harder and more complex concepts, making it feel like a level 200 course. He is very cocky to his students at times as well.
Literally the worst professor i have ever had. doesn't answer e-mails, isn't in his office during office hours. Study your book and you'll be fine. He makes a lot of mistakes in class as well.
Awesome guy, great artist. Very intelligent, knows how to guide you creatively. His lectures give sparks to the imagination, and his mannerisms and guidance end giving a fantastic final product.
Took Drawing - very easy-going professor. Nice, wants you to do well, easy grader. Funny. If you can get a drawing class with him I recommend it.
I miss his class and wish he was still here. I miss just talkin to the dude. He was great.
Best professor ever! I would have taken all my classes with him if I had the chance. He is honest and a grear person.
I had heard so much about grimm and now he isn't here I feel like I was cheated. I can't believe etown laid him off. I missed out.
What stupid decision by etown to let Grimm go. He will be missed.
Easily the best professor I have had so far and I have learned so much more in one semester than in high school. And he cares so much.

Grimm can be a tough grader and give harsh feedback but it's because he wants you to learn and succeed. He offers extra credit so if you get bad grades on the first couple papers you can make them up. He is funny and a fun guy so I really looked forward to his class even though I hate English. Can seem intimidating but is really a nice guy.
Obviously take one of Grimm's classes.

Grimm is a nice guy at heart, but he is a very tough grader from my perspective. If you don't write well, he will shred your papers apart (not literally). He is helpful in some ways and understands that not everyone is a great writer or can be one. Also, be prepared to read.

I would definitely choose him over other EN 100 professors (from what I've heard anyway). He's VERY clear on what he wants and gives straightforward criticisms. He's funny, so lectures are fun. Be ready to discuss. He often hands back assignments very late, but also wants the best for you. If you have any concerns, feel free to go talk to him. ^^

I would definitely choose him over other EN 100 professors (from what I've heard anyway). He's VERY clear on what he wants and gives straightforward criticisms. He's funny, so lectures are fun. Be ready to discuss. He often hands back assignments very late, but also wants the best for you. If you have any concerns, feel free to go talk to him.
what a beautiful man
Loved this class. Grimm made english fun. He can be harsh on you in his feedback but not necesarily a hard grader. He wants you to grow and improve and thats what he really looks for.
I loved him as a professor and an adviser. There were times when the class was disorganized though. But still fun.

He's a good professor, but you have to write the way he wants you to. I wrote many papers in there, and when I wrote for him I earned a good grade. When I wrote my own, I got deducted many points. Many published authors have written similarly to things that lost me points in this class. Just be prepared to write in one specific style

Grimm is an excellent teacher who truly knows and understands his craft. But what separates him from any other intelligent, well-versed professor is that he is actually able to get the information across in a way students can understand no matter their skill level. He has ignited my passion for writing, and I can't wait to take more of his classes.
The professor is one of the most understanding amongst my first year at Elizabethtown College. He made an 8 am class in my very first semester fun and educational.

Tyler Grimm is the coolest professor I've ever had. Down to earth, very helpful, and an absolute sweetheart. His feedback is very critical to your success in his class, and he can be hard on you, only because deep down he really cares about your progression in writing.

Really great professor. He's one of those professors you can be friends with once you get to know him. He'll encourage whatever you want to write, as long as you do it correctly. Even though sometimes he can be harsh in his feedback, it's very constructive and immensely helpful. You'll never use "that" again in any writing after his class as well.

Professor Grimm's class was by far one of the most exciting of this semester. He cares so much about his students and is super laid-back and chill. :) His final is just a revision of all the writing you've done in class so nothing too worry about. You hardly use the text books you buy for his class. He promotes creativity:) Take his class! :)

Andy was my favorite professor at Elizabethtown. I had him for four different classes in my undergrad career. I appreciated him as a person and professor. Very supportive, gives good feedback, open-minded, and willing to listen to any questions/concerns. He isn't a tough grader but he does expect quality work. I highly recommend him!

Dr. Dunlap is hit or miss, there are times where he puts on a great lecture & shows a true interest in the topic. It was noticed that he doesn't always read papers / make edits. That was frustrating for me because I worked hard on a 20 page paper and he pretty much gave everyone a B+. Had another SW Professor taught the class I would have opted out
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria

comment: Seriously a great professor. He is very clear with the material that he is teaching and does a lot of discussing with the students. He makes sure that you understand the material before you leave the room. He requires a lot, but he breaks everything up pretty well so you're not overwhelmed. I knew he would be great from the start!
I love Read-Daily. She is so nice, the only issue is she doesn't help when you are confused. She tries but is usually vague and unclear.
Although the class was simple enough, I could never get a clear answer to any of my questions from her. It was always a run around, and never really got what I asked for.

I have had Dr. Read-Daily multiple times since she first became a professor at E-Town.  It has been amazing to watch her grow as a professor.  Each year, she is becoming more confident in her teaching abilities, while finding new and better ways to help students learn the course material.  She is an excellent professor and role model!

Dr.Read-Daily was one of the best professors I've had at Elizabethtown College. She presented the material in a very interesting way that actually made me excited to go to 8 A.M. Physics 3 every day. She's willing to help and cares a lot about how her students are doing. Even though she's relatively new to teaching she is great at what she does.
Great class! Really teaches you the three main differences in writing. Great teacher! Won't make the hour and a half feel as long.
Grading yourself was really nice. We only had to write 2 papers, but I still feel like I learned a lot.
Great class! Loved it. Jeff is awesome!
He's very understanding about how busy the school semester is, always there to help, and is funny.
Was an a different English class than I have ever taken before I liked the way he went about it and had us create the book I really enjoyed the class.
The class may not seem like much, but it is a huge deal! I'm so glad I had this while taking my FYS because it saved my butt when writing the term paper!

I enjoyed this class because it's like nothing I experienced in high school. Prof. Minton is a down-to-earth teacher and easy to get along with. I found that most of his assignments were very helpful and that he truly wanted his students to become better writers. You won't regret being in his class!
This is EXACTLY how an English 100 class should be ran!

Minton is a very good teacher and it was very nice to have his class this semester.  The class is really easy and you only have to write two papers throughout the whole semester.  Even if you do bad on the papers, you can still pass.

I really enjoyed this class! Professor Minton was hilarious, but still managed to teach us some useful and interesting things! If I could I would take another class taught by him. I overall i enjoyed his class and recommend anyone at E-town have him as an english professor.

I went in to this class with a bad attitude towards taking a mandatory English class, but, the classroom setup is very different from that of a high school. He really promotes the students to be creative and take charge of their learning. Your term grade is based on your own self evaluations.
He's the best professor! Take this class to full your core curriculum. You won't regret it!

Literally one of the most confusing professors I have ever had. He procrastinates so much with assignments and never clarifies anything. He also goes into way too much detail with what he teaches and is a tough grader. But, he answers emails pretty quickly and gives out lots of grades so there's always room to get extra points.

One large paper and three tests.  The professor breaks the paper down into manageable drafts to turn in but the comments aren't much help.  Isn't much help to prepare for tests and class is very boring.

Dr. Chen is a great prof and is extremely smart at what she does. She takes time to explain everything going on in class, or if you have questions. The class is lecture heavy and reading the book is very helpful. However, if you ask questions, you will do just fine. We will be sad to see her go, but wish her luck at her new school.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Clear grading criteria--Lecture heavy

comment: Lectures every class. Occasional "pop" quizzes that you'll pass if you look over the reading. Overall, an easy class.

Mostly a lecture class with powerpoints you can access from canvas. Throughout the class there's a group project that takes the whole semester but it's really easy if your group agrees on what to present. She's a really good person but some of her lectures are boring and since we can have laptops I usually wonder off from the powerpoint.

You'll have a group paper. It's all PowerPoint and lecture. If you ask a question she'll just repeat what's on the slide. Not as bad as international relations with her. Boring. Be prepared to regurgitate information for the tests. Overall easy, but it's part of my major so may be different if taking for core.
Dr. Chen is a amazing professor, but International Relations is not her area of expertise.  If you get a chance, take her Comparative Politics class instead of International Relations with here.

Dan is a good professor who really knows her stuff. If you need help outside of class, she is willing to help.  Her lectures are really long and boring so bring your computer to class and surf the web. Tests can be a bit tricky but is an easy grader. Would definitely take this class again with her.

Probably one of the hardest classes Ive ever taken but Gabriel is still the best professor ever and he makes the class interesting even if its hard. Cost accounting is now engraved into my brain even though i suck at it, hes also a real help in office hours. Pretty tough on you but its because he cares. And dont crack your knuckles around him

Professor Gabriel is one of the best professors I have had. He makes his lectures interesting and really cares about his students. Just make sure to attend class because he will notice if you regularly skip. He is also really funny!
Gabriel is a tough teacher (probably because Accounting is tough, and I hated accounting). But, he is a nice guy and if you speak and show that you need help, he will help you.
I love professor Gabriel. He demands a lot of his students but you will really learn.  He acts scary and tough but he is actually a teddy bear

Dr. Yeagley is a tough lab professor. However, after two semesters with him, I can honestly say that this man was a great lab professor. If you take him for ochem 1, you will understand how he works and can take him again for ochem 2.
Awful instructor. Grades assignments like students have PhD.s in Chemistry. Funny guy, but you will not do well in his lab. Nobody does. Even straight A students get C's on every assignment
Do not take. You will not do well. Nobody does. Straight A student and failed all three papers. Grading criteria is impossible. If you don't write how he would, you will not do well.
Great class to take. Dr. K is clearly in the zone in this class, and obviously loves teaching it. Very understand with deadlines and will work with you to succeed.

Con Law I was great with Dr. Kopko! I would highly recommend taking this course, especially if you have any inclination of attending law school. It will definitely shed light on the type of experience you will have there.
She's a great professor, highly recommend you to take her !!!

She's super funny, chill, and loves what she teaches. If you want help, you gotta reach out yourself but she will be there. She's very open minded. Participation matters a lot. Do your work and if she gives you feedback, follow them.

Even though this was not my primary choice of FYS, I am really glad I got it and Dr. Milligan is the reason. She makes everything very clear, is passionate about what she is teaching, is funny, and is willing to help when you ask for it.

He is very knowledgeable about the subject & clarifies complicated concepts. After taking this class, I have more respect for the psychology field. If you participate in discussions, do the readings, and study the powerpoints, you will do fine.
Interesting class. Lots of fieldwork which is what the course was about. Quizzes don't count for much but add up. Stay on top of assignments and its manageable.
This man is absolutely nuts and I love him. His life is chaos.
This was a good course. Professor is organized and funny. Most of the lectures are interesting.

He's a good professor, you just have to do the readings and keep up with them.  There was stuff on the tests that he didn't mention in lectures that were in the book.  The only assignments were the midterm, final, and a group projectpresentation.

Dr. St. Vil is an amazing professor. She makes difficult boring classes worth attending and actually interesting. Her grading is easy and as long as you put in the work, you will receive a good grade in her class. She is accessible and caring... she definitely wants her students to succeed and cares about your mental status throughout the semester.

Noelle is an amazing teacher who cares about her students. For the last few weeks of the course, we didn't even have class so that we could work on our group projects, but she is knowledgeable enough that we didn't need to have class all that time because we learned quickly with her. Very helpful smart and kind.

Good teacher, can be a bit of a pushover when it comes to due dates.  She's nice, but doesn't always seem super personable and open about herself.  She gives good lectures and the powerpoint is a great supplement.

Dr. Newton is the best professor i have had at Etown. He really cares about his students and will make sure you do well. Go to his office hours!! He is so helpful and he rewards you for trying! His lectures are so interesting and you learn so much more than you think you are.

Dr. Newton is one of the best professors at Etown! He has a way of explaining things so clearly that by the end of the semester you are able to connect the dots on your own and create your own arguments. The things you learn in his class with stay with you for a long, long time. He makes you work for your grade, and expect lots of homework though.

He's a really great professor. He helps you the best he can, but only if you show him you care. If you don't care he's not going to help you. He's not strict like some other professors but don't take advantage of that because good things won't come out if it. If you want to do well in his class, then you have to work hard.

Dr. Newton is an amazing professor and I learned a lot from his Signifying Religion 101 class. He is always willing to go out of his way to help you and he is very passionate about what he teaches. This class is a lot of work, specifically when it comes to reading. However, the work is enjoyable, and his teaching method is one that works.

Dr. Newton was the best professor I had at Etown. He was so helpful in office hours, super clear in his rubrics, and led very interesting lectures. He almost made me want to become a Religion major. He loves his subject and teaches his material well. Would definitely take again.

This is a conversational class. You basically sit around a table and talk in French, so if you have a high level of French you'll do well. If you can only say "bonjour" then it'll be a rough semester. Madame Borilot is so sweet and encouraging. Her class is a safe space to make mistakes and she has fun activities.
Excellent
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Very good class. Attendance is important, and it is always good to participate! Very nice as a person and a professor.
She's hot and she made French seem easier than when I took it in high school.
Professor Borilot is very helpful when you need it. She gives good advice and cares about the students and what they need.

Dr. Borilot is an awesome professor, she's the best french professor here at Etown. I believe she's willing to help anyone no matter any issue. I enjoyed her 2 upper 300 level french classes. Her teaching style is very positive and engaging, I would recommend someone interested  in taking a french class with her.
This professor gave a lot of coursework but was very helpful with her feedback and was always available to ask her any questions.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Get ready to do a lot of translating. There is typically a translation each night for homework, along with a quiz usually every class. She takes grammar very seriously. She tries to be funny but her comments to students are often insulting. She's very email happy and will email you if you have the slightest issue with something.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: - difficult grader, if you don't do everything she wants, don't expect to get a good grade - rubrics for every paper, stick to them - grammar is important, stick to the Pocket Style Manual - proper citation is important - check Canvas frequently to stay up-to-date on assignments - lots of reading - shows no mercy in grading - be prepared

Dr. Freet does not use the textbooks listed in the syllabus for his lectures or exams. He requires you to know information from a 300 level Cell Biology course for this 100 level Psychology course, INTRODUCTION to Neuroscience.

This class is very interesting, however Freet seems to be relatively new to teaching still and does not have the best method. For instance he simply reads through the lengthy power points word by word. Review classes are even worse because its just rereading the power points. Tests are extremely difficult and require a very deep knowledge.
He only reads from the powerpoints and his "study guides" don't help at all. You literally have to know everything for the tests. It's an interesting class but don't take it with this professor.

Professor Freet reads straight from the power point and his lectures are a bit dry. When it comes to taking the exams, you really need to know your stuff. His questions are very specific so be prepared for anything.

Dr. Licona is a really chill dude who interacts with his students. There are a lot of projects but they're fairly easy assignments. He will work with you no matter what. Great guy and a relatively easy class.
Awesome dude! Lets you do the talking and learning. Loves the smell of skunks!!
She's very caring about students' grade and progress of the class. It is very helpful to ask her help for projects.
Knows what she is talking about but does not know how to convey the knowledge to her students.
she's incredibly sweet and intelligent but is absolutely horrible at explaining even the simplest of concepts.

This is her first year so this is taking it a little easy, but she has a really hard time teaching the content. I knew the content already, but I noticed a lot of other students not grasping very simple concepts because she could not properly explain it, nor could she understand students questions and would end up answering them wrong.

She is knowledgable in her field but has a very difficult time relaying the material to her students. Her lectures are very boring and sometimes hard to understand. Each class is the same, she stands at the front of the room and just talks for the full hour and 20 minutes. Quizzes and tests are easy, though, as long as you read the book.
DR. Ajay is an amazing professor. He's very detailed in his lectures and helps out outside of class via email. An easy A.
Good professor!

Dr. Hughes is super friendly and patient (and has a relaxing vibe to her - soothing voice). Ask for help whenever you need it! She replies back to emails very quickly and offers great feedback. The way she grades projects is pretty easy. As long as you follow the rubric and do your best, you can easily get a 100% on it. Overall, a great professor!

She's a pretty good teacher. I've had her for both my years here at the college. Depending upon the class, you may end up using the book or not using it. The book is a must for COM130, but not so much COM210. A very sociable professor.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Participation matters

comment: Sweetest person. Very helpful with everything and always trying to give you the benefit of the doubt. Easy grader, but attendance is very important to her. Nicest lady ever. Almost every quiz or exam has opportunities for extra credit.

Class was a total joke She's a good teacher, but the material was very easy. She was very patient with students who were too dense to listen and wait until she told them how to do stuff. She's a very easy grader, I had above a 100% for most of the semester and gives you 100% on projects as long as you met the criteria regardless of how bad it looks
young professor, easy class. my honors English classes in high school were more difficult. she loves to have class debates which can be interesting. I would take this if you want an easy class :)
ratingTags: Participation matters--Tests? Not many--Would take again

comment: she lets you rewrite any paper for a better grade. you just have to be willing to do your paper over again until it's an A. I personally thought sometimes the paper guidelines were confusing and for some assignments she took a few weeks to get the grade in, but overall the class was easy. Just do the work
ratingTags: Tough Grader--Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: the only class I took where the professor didn't talk the whole time. Professor Daubenspeck wants you to speak up and discuss  the readings and write and share what you wrote in class. She'll let you revise any paper and gives lengthy feedback you can actually use.  She's approachable and funny, I enjoyed this class and would recommend

Professor Daubenspeck has a tendency to play favorites in her class, she gives good feedback on papers, but will literally correct your paper for you and then say that there are still mistakes (even in the parts she rewrote for you), and she sometimes treats her classes with little respect (although admittedly my class would have annoyed me too.)
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--Gives good feedback

comment: I am ecstatic over the fact that I had this opportunity to take such an informative class taught by such a knowledgeable and inspirational person.  I would encourage anyone to take any class this professor teaches.  I absolutely feel that  I have benefited from having this class and having this professor.  I feel extremely fortunate!  Thank you!

Dr. Amoroso is a horrible professor. I'm saying this with respect. He should not be teaching. He gives no partial credit and is very poor in lecture. I haven't learned a thing from him, which isn't good for an Organic Chemistry class. If other schools are reading this, DO NOT HIRE THIS MAN AS A REPLACEMENT PROF!!!!!!!!!!!!

honestly this guy sucks as an organic prof and he cant teach to save his life. his exams are like what, only 8 questions each worth 20 points??? hes a tough grader and really picky, and hell tell you that hell give partial credit but thats a complete and total lie. if you have the option between him and someone else CHOOSE SOMEONE ELSE!

Had him for an online class. Most work I've ever done. This dude has 3 assignments due everyday. Then he has bigger written assignments on top of that. I would never take another class with him. I would never recommend him to anybody. If you take his online class and have a job, your life will suck for 6 weeks.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Clear grading criteria--Tough grader

comment: Dr. MacFarlane is a great professor! His class was not easy, but VERY rewarding. His test require you to know the lecture information (and textbook readings) inside and out (so do NOT study the night before and read your book!!!). A few papers (that have clear grading criteria) and outside of class video lectures were included.

It seems like Dr. Caprino's personal priority is to make sure all her students like her, and that tends to turn us off. When arguing a grade on a project, she specifically said a rubric is "a guide" and should not be looked at as a checklist, this goes against basically everything we learned in our assessment course.

Caprino is amazing. She's sweet, passionate, and cares about her students and their future students. She gives you everything you need to study. Tests are online, as are most quizzes. She prepared us for ED151and Provisional Acceptance.
Awesome teacher. Really engaged with her students and walks you through the assignments. If you took AP Lit in high school, this will be a piece of cake. Very nice person overall.

EN100 with Dolson is easy, just extremely repetitive. I came from a really strong writing background, and her EN100 class was just a review. Group work in class is forced, which can be frustrating. Overall, really easy, but extremely boring.
ratingTags: Clear grading criteria--Gives good feedback--Participation matters

comment: I would not recommend taking a class with Professor Moore, from my personal experience as well as numerous other students, she is unclear and does not explain assignments and material well. Along with not explaining material well to her students, she rarely helps students and is very rude. completing tasks is difficult as she doesn't grade clearly
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--So many papers--Tough grader

comment: Hands-down one of the sweetest teachers I have ever had. I think the textbook was listed as required, but you could probably get by w/o it. However, you probably need the 40 studies book. Weekly reading is assigned. If you aren't going to do it, at least read the 40 studies. Class goes by a lot quicker when you just participate in the discussion.

Dr. Caprino is calm and laid-back; I favor him a lot! Assigned homework is chapter readings in the textbook. The main things he grades are quizzes, tests, and a group project. He doesn't take attendance, but I would still suggest going to class to fully understand each concept. It's easy to receive an A in this class if you pay attention and study.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Graded by few things--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Kris is unusual for ETown but thats not automatically a bad thing. She cares a lot and is willing to adjust class, but may get lost sometimes trying to cater to students too much. Her heart is in a good place, and she knows a lot- I would take another class again.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Inspirational

comment: she was a awful professor and had no knowledge of the Justice system. she was unclear on all everything and just made up stuff as she went. she would not answer emails or would not want to meet with any of her students.

I really enjoyed Kris' class. As a young person herself, she is able to relate to students in terms of preparing to enter graduate school and/or the professional job market. She makes herself available to students for things like getting references after graduation and reviewing resumes. The more you reach out, the more you'll get from her course!

The 100 course I took with her was super hard, but it was one of my favorites. She teaches really in-depth and is really interesting. I wouldn't recommend it for anyone who hates history or is just filling a core. There's tons of reading and you have to pay attention well to get an A or B. She offers awesome feedback and is a great instructor.

Dr. Densford makes this 100 level class very difficult. She does not believe in providing useful powerpoints with notes, she only puts pictures on the slides. She reads directly off a paper and expects you to write down word for word what she says. My notebook is already full. There are basically no grades for this class and you read 5 books.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: Brian started off as a really strong professor, talking about the stuff a real software engineer does . However none of that ever happened, as the semester progressed his lectures became incoherent, the quizzes were ridiculous and irrelevant to the class and the entire class just became the group project. Made the room smell like cigarette smoke.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Graded by few things--Group projects

comment: Brian is an excellent professor. He is extremely excited about the material, he wants the students to succeed and he is obsessed with giving students real world experience. It has been refreshing to take a course where more emphasis is put on learning the material rather than getting a good grade.

Great class to get beyond power points. Yes there are power points, but professor Schmid goes beyond them and gives his first hand experiences in the business world. More specifically he gives examples of times hes failed and what he learned from those failures. If you show up youll do just fine.
Great professor! He really made the subject easy to understand with examples and homework. The exams were all scantron too. Overall laid back and very easy to get along with

Dr. Poole is caring and makes it clear that she's available to help you. Most of the homework assigned are readings. Her lectures compose of talking and going through slides while you take notes. Also, she calls on people often. Main issue is she doesn't explain content clearly during lectures, but you can ask for clarification through email.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Caring

comment: Dr. Haffejee is one of the most understanding and caring person I've ever met. She doesn't call on people; however, participation is graded. She is interested in hearing people's thoughts on topics. Assigned homework consist of reading chapters in the textbook. Her lectures compose of slides and doing a lot of group work (seriously, a lot).

Professor Biever is willing to help you if you make the effort to ask for help. She's really caring and a pretty tough grader when it comes to essays though (all out of 200 points). Attendance is taken, but four absences are allowed. She'll tell you ahead of time when a pop quiz is coming up. Assigned homework is grammar exercises and readings.

Lectures are a waste of time but count for a huge chunk of your final grade. Homework will be insanely hard and I recommend investing in Chegg otherwise they will take hours and you'll get terrible grades on the problems
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.--Tough grader

comment: This was actually one of my favorite classes last semester. She is an adjunct but super dedicated to helping you and reading your papers before you turn them in. She tells a lot of stories from her work in the community to give examples of theories, which is helpful. If you read, hand in your work, show up to class and participate you're good!

Dr. Sigdel is friendly and approachable. There are lots of lectures and note-taking, and homework consist of problems on WebWork. A textbook isn't needed. He replies back to emails quickly. If you need help, ask away! He's patient and doesn't make you feel awful about yourself for not knowing the material. Overall, a great professor!
